[4] Cholera - Worldwide: WHO WER Notifications
Date: Fri 16 Jul 2004
From: Marianne Hopp <mjhopp12@yahoo.com>
Source: WHO Epidemiological Record, 16 Jul 2004 [edited]
<http://www.who.int/wer/2004/wer7928/en/>

Corrigendum, TO No. 28, 2004
----------------------------------
The cases of cholera that Japan reported in the last issue were all
imported, and there were no fatalities.
Notifications of cholera received from 9 - 15 Jul 2004
country / date / cases / deaths
Africa:
Burundi / 19 Jun-4 Jul 2004 / 82 / 4
Tanzania / 26 Jun-2 Jul 2004 / 12 / 0
Zimbabwe / 21-27 Jun 2004 / 1 / 0
Asia:
Singapore / 16 Jun 2004 / 1(i) / 0
(i) = imported
[****Request for information**** It should be noted that the WHO reports
that an imported case of cholera was imported to Singapore on 16 Jun 2004.
We would appreciate information regarding this observation. - Mod.LL]
